{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0172rA9ABNvykkNjLzrkFcUi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Dc2WxcxvGCBgaDj3jkKsV","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8153,"cache_read_input_tokens":25781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8153,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019ny8ECB7uLgXDKVNYx1sev","session_id":"e1f3df9b-d919-466e-880e-1001c8652ee8","uuid":"0bb90d45-ab84-4b93-8ba5-80ee992d2fac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Dc2WxcxvGCBgaDj3jkKsV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→stepsCompleted: [1, 2]\n     3→lastStep: 2\n     4→status: complete\n     5→completedAt: '2026-03-17'\n     6→inputDocuments:\n     7→  - prd-overhaul.md\n     8→  - product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md\n     9→  - ux-design-specification.md (v1, reworked)\n    10→workflowType: 'ux-design'\n    11→note: 'Full CLI UX spec — reworked for architecture overhaul with status visibility, failure detail, live mode'\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→# CLI UX Specification — codeharness (v2)\n    15→\n    16→**Date:** 2026-03-17\n    17→**Revision:** Architecture overhaul — reworked for visibility, responsiveness, and clear failure reporting\n    18→\n    19→## Overview\n    20→\n    21→codeharness is a CLI tool. No GUI, no web interface, no visual design. The UX is the developer experience in the terminal: command output, error messages, progress reporting, hook feedback, and proof document structure.\n    22→\n    23→**Core UX principle:** One screen, full picture. Progressive detail. Failures are specific and actionable.\n    24→\n    25→**Target user:** Developer who runs codeharness and checks back later. Needs to understand what happened in 10 seconds, drill into failures in 2 minutes, and never spelunk through log files.\n    26→\n    27→## Command Surface\n    28→\n    29→```\n    30→codeharness <command> [options]\n    31→\n    32→Commands:\n    33→  init        Initialize harness in current project\n    34→  run         Start autonomous execution loop\n    35→  verify      Run verification pipeline for a story\n    36→  status      Show project state, run progress, and action items\n    37→  bridge      Import BMAD stories into beads\n    38→  onboard     Scan existing project and generate onboarding plan\n    39→  teardown    Remove harness artifacts (preserves project code)\n    40→  state       Read/write harness state flags\n    41→  retry       Manage story retry state\n    42→\n    43→Options:\n    44→  --json      Machine-readable JSON output (all commands)\n    45→  --verbose   Verbose output for debugging\n    46→  --help      Show help\n    47→  --version   Show version\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→### Command-Specific Options\n    51→\n    52→```\n    53→codeharness init [--no-observability] [--no-frontend] [--no-database] [--no-api]\n    54→                 [--opensearch-url <url>]\n    55→                 [--otel-endpoint <url>]\n    56→                 [--logs-url <url>] [--metrics-url <url>] [--traces-url <url>]\n    57→codeharness run  [--live] [--stop] [--max-iterations <n>] [--timeout <seconds>]\n    58→codeharness verify --story <story-id>\n    59→codeharness status [--story <id>] [--check-docker]\n    60→codeharness bridge --epics <path> [--dry-run]\n    61→codeharness onboard [scan|coverage|audit|epic] [--project-dir <path>]\n    62→codeharness teardown [--keep-docker] [--keep-beads]\n    63→codeharness state [get <key>|set <key> <value>|reset]\n    64→codeharness retry [--status] [--reset] [--reset --story <id>] [--json]\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→## Output Patterns\n    68→\n    69→### Status Prefixes\n    70→\n    71→Every line of output uses a prefix:\n    72→\n    73→```\n    74→[OK]   Successfully completed action\n    75→[FAIL] Action failed — followed by actionable remedy\n    76→[WARN] Non-fatal issue — something to be aware of\n    77→[INFO] Informational — progress update or context\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→### Symbols for Live/Status Views\n    81→\n    82→```\n    83→✓  completed successfully\n    84→✗  failed\n    85→◆  in progress\n    86→○  pending\n    87→✕  blocked/exhausted\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→## Command UX: `codeharness status`\n    91→\n    92→### Default Output (One Screen)\n    93→\n    94→```\n    95→codeharness v0.18.1 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n    96→\n    97→── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n    98→Sprint: 17/65 done (26%) | 5/16 epics complete\n    99→Current epic: Epic 3 — BMAD Integration (2/4 stories done)\n   100→Modules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n   101→\n   102→── Active Run ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   103→Status: running (iteration 7, 2h14m elapsed)\n   104→Current: 3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge → verifying (AC 4/7)\n   105→Last action: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness bridge --dry-run\n   106→Budget: $23.40 spent | 47 stories remaining\n   107→\n   108→── This Run ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   109→Completed:  4 stories (3-1, 3-2, 4-1, 4-2)\n   110→Failed:     1 story\n   111→  └ 2-3: AC 4 — status --check-docker exit 1 (attempt 3/10)\n   112→Blocked:    2 stories\n   113→  └ 0-1: retry-exhausted (10/10)\n   114→  └ 13-3: retry-exhausted (10/10)\n   115→Skipped:    3 stories (retry-exhausted)\n   116→In progress: 1 story (3-3)\n   117→\n   118→── Action Items (this run) ────────────────────────────────────\n   119→NEW: 2-3 needs fix: status checks project-level containers, not shared\n   120→CARRIED: A56 status --check-docker wrong containers (3 sessions)\n   121→```\n   122→\n   123→### No Active Run\n   124→\n   125→```\n   126→codeharness v0.18.1 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n   127→\n   128→── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n   129→Sprint: 17/65 done (26%) | 5/16 epics complete\n   130→Last run: 2h14m ago (4 completed, 1 failed, 2 blocked)\n   131→Modules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n   132→\n   133→── Last Run Summary ───────────────────────────────────────────\n   134→Duration: 2h14m | Cost: $23.40 | Iterations: 7\n   135→Completed:  4 stories (3-1, 3-2, 4-1, 4-2)\n   136→Failed:     1 story\n   137→  └ 2-3: AC 4 — status --check-docker exit 1 (attempt 3/10)\n   138→Blocked:    2 stories (retry-exhausted)\n   139→Skipped:    3 stories\n   140→\n   141→── Action Items ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n   142→[1] FIX 2-3: status checks project-level containers, not shared stack\n   143→[2] CARRIED A56: status --check-docker wrong containers (3 sessions)\n   144→\n   145→→ Run: codeharness status --story 2-3 for details\n   146→→ Run: codeharness run to resume\n   147→```\n   148→\n   149→### Story Drill-Down: `codeharness status --story <id>`\n   150→\n   151→```\n   152→Story: 2-3-observability-querying-agent-visibility-into-runtime\n   153→Status: failed (attempt 3/10)\n   154→Epic: 2 — Observability Stack\n   155→Last attempt: 2026-03-18T03:42:15Z\n   156→\n   157→── AC Results ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   158→AC 1: [PASS] VictoriaLogs query returns structured logs\n   159→AC 2: [PASS] VictoriaMetrics query returns metrics\n   160→AC 3: [PASS] Agent queries logs during dev workflow\n   161→AC 4: [FAIL] Status command reports stack health correctly\n   162→  Command:  docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness status --check-docker\n   163→  Expected: exit 0 with \"running\" for all services\n   164→  Actual:   exit 1\n   165→  Output:   [FAIL] VictoriaMetrics stack: not running\n   166→  Reason:   Checks project-level container names (codeharness-victoria-logs-1)\n   167→            but shared stack uses (codeharness-shared-victoria-logs-1)\n   168→  Suggest:  Fix container name matching in src/commands/status.ts\n   169→AC 5: [PASS] Query endpoints accessible from verification container\n   170→AC 6: [ESCALATE] Observability data persists across sessions\n   171→AC 7: [PASS] OTLP instrumentation auto-configured\n   172→\n   173→── History ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   174→Attempt 1: verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n   175→Attempt 2: dev fix applied → verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n   176→Attempt 3: dev fix applied → verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n   177→\n   178→Proof: verification/2-3-proof.md (5/7 pass, 1 fail, 1 escalate)\n   179→```\n   180→\n   181→## Command UX: `codeharness run`\n   182→\n   183→### Default (Background with Status File)\n   184→\n   185→```\n   186→$ codeharness run\n   187→[INFO] Starting autonomous execution — 6 ready, 1 in progress, 42 verifying\n   188→[INFO] Observability: shared stack running (VictoriaMetrics)\n   189→[INFO] Verification container: ready\n   190→\n   191→Running in background. Check progress:\n   192→  → codeharness status          (one-screen summary)\n   193→  → codeharness run --live      (streaming output)\n   194→  → codeharness run --stop      (graceful stop after current story)\n   195→```\n   196→\n   197→### Live Mode: `codeharness run --live`\n   198→\n   199→Rolling status that updates in place:\n   200→\n   201→```\n   202→$ codeharness run --live\n   203→\n   204→codeharness run | iteration 3 | 47m elapsed | $12.30 spent\n   205→━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n   206→Story: 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching\n   207→Phase: verify → AC 8/12 (docker exec ... codeharness init --json)\n   208→\n   209→Done: 3-1 ✓  4-1 ✓  4-2 ✓\n   210→This: 3-2 ◆ verifying (8/12 ACs)\n   211→Next: 3-3 (verifying, no proof yet)\n   212→\n   213→Blocked: 0-1 ✕ (10/10)  13-3 ✕ (10/10)\n   214→━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n   215→```\n   216→\n   217→### Story Completes\n   218→\n   219→```\n   220→[OK] Story 3-2: DONE — 12/12 ACs verified\n   221→  └ Proof: verification/3-2-proof.md\n   222→  └ Duration: 18m | Cost: $4.20\n   223→[INFO] Sprint: 18/65 done (28%) — moving to 3-3\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→### Story Returned to Dev\n   227→\n   228→```\n   229→[WARN] Story 3-3: verification found 2 failing ACs → returning to dev\n   230→  └ AC 3: bridge --dry-run output missing epic headers\n   231→  └ AC 7: bridge creates duplicate beads issues\n   232→  └ Attempt 2/10 — dev will fix and re-verify\n   233→```\n   234→\n   235→### Story Failed\n   236→\n   237→```\n   238→[FAIL] Story 2-3: verification failed at AC 4 (attempt 3/10)\n   239→  └ docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness status --check-docker → exit 1\n   240→  └ Output: \"[FAIL] VictoriaMetrics stack: not running\"\n   241→  └ Returning to dev for fix (attempt 4)\n   242→[INFO] Moving to next story: 3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge\n   243→```\n   244→\n   245→### Timeout\n   246→\n   247→```\n   248→[WARN] Story 5-2: verification timed out after 30m (attempt 2/10)\n   249→  └ Partial proof saved: verification/5-2-proof.md (3/7 ACs before timeout)\n   250→  └ Git changes captured: 2 files modified\n   251→  └ Moving to next story\n   252→```\n   253→\n   254→## Command UX: `codeharness init`\n   255→\n   256→### Successful Init\n   257→\n   258→```\n   259→$ codeharness init\n   260→\n   261→── Stack Detection ────────────────────────────────────────────\n   262→[OK] Stack: Node.js (package.json)\n   263→[OK] App type: CLI\n   264→\n   265→── Dependencies ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n   266→[OK] Docker: running\n   267→[OK] Showboat: installed (v0.6.1)\n   268→[OK] agent-browser: installed (v1.2.0)\n   269→[OK] OTLP: Node.js packages installed\n   270→\n   271→── Observability ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n   272→[OK] Shared stack: already running at ~/.codeharness/stack/\n   273→     └ VictoriaLogs :9428  VictoriaMetrics :8428  OTel :4318\n   274→\n   275→── BMAD ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   276→[OK] BMAD: installed (v6.2.0)\n   277→[OK] Patches: 5 applied (story, dev, review, retro, sprint)\n   278→\n   279→── Project Setup ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n   280→[OK] State: .claude/codeharness.local.md created\n   281→[OK] Docs: AGENTS.md + docs/ scaffold created\n   282→[OK] Enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n   283→\n   284→Ready. Run: codeharness run\n   285→```\n   286→\n   287→### Init with OpenSearch\n   288→\n   289→```\n   290→$ codeharness init --opensearch-url https://search.example.com\n   291→\n   292→── Observability ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n   293→[OK] OpenSearch: connected (https://search.example.com)\n   294→     └ Logs: ✓  Metrics: ✓  Traces: ✓\n   295→[INFO] No local Docker stack needed — using remote OpenSearch\n   296→```\n   297→\n   298→### Init Failure (Actionable)\n   299→\n   300→```\n   301→$ codeharness init\n   302→\n   303→── Dependencies ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n   304→[OK] Docker: running\n   305→[FAIL] Showboat: not found\n   306→       → Install: pip install showboat\n   307→       → Or: uv tool install showboat\n   308→[OK] OTLP: Node.js packages installed\n   309→\n   310→── Observability ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n   311→[WARN] Port 9428 already in use\n   312→       → Shared stack may be running from another project\n   313→       → Check: docker compose -p codeharness-shared ps\n   314→       → Or use remote: codeharness init --opensearch-url <url>\n   315→```\n   316→\n   317→## Command UX: `codeharness verify --story <id>`\n   318→\n   319→### During Verification (Streaming)\n   320→\n   321→```\n   322→$ codeharness verify --story 3-2\n   323→\n   324→[INFO] Story: 3-2-bmad-installation-workflow-patching (12 ACs)\n   325→[INFO] Preparing verification container...\n   326→[OK] Container: codeharness-verify ready\n   327→[OK] Clean workspace: /tmp/codeharness-verify-3-2/\n   328→\n   329→Verifying ACs:\n   330→  AC  1: ✓ BMAD installs via npx bmad-method install\n   331→  AC  2: ✓ _bmad/ directory created with correct structure\n   332→  AC  3: ✓ BMAD version detected from module.yaml\n   333→  AC  4: ◆ Running... (docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness init)\n   334→```\n   335→\n   336→### Verification Complete\n   337→\n   338→```\n   339→  AC 12: ✓ Re-run detects existing install and verifies patches\n   340→\n   341→[OK] Story 3-2: 12/12 ACs verified\n   342→[OK] Proof: verification/3-2-proof.md\n   343→[OK] Sprint status: 3-2 → done\n   344→\n   345→Duration: 14m | Cost: $3.80\n   346→```\n   347→\n   348→### Verification Failed\n   349→\n   350→```\n   351→  AC  4: ✗ FAIL — status --check-docker exit 1\n   352→         Output: \"[FAIL] VictoriaMetrics stack: not running\"\n   353→  AC  5: ✓ Query endpoints accessible\n   354→  ...\n   355→  AC 12: ✓ Re-run verifies patches\n   356→\n   357→[FAIL] Story 2-3: 5/7 ACs verified, 1 failed, 1 escalated\n   358→[INFO] Proof: verification/2-3-proof.md (partial)\n   359→[INFO] Story returned to in-progress for dev fix\n   360→\n   361→→ Run: codeharness status --story 2-3 for failure details\n   362→```\n   363→\n   364→## Proof Document UX\n   365→\n   366→### Standard Proof (Docker Exec)\n   367→\n   368→```markdown\n   369→## AC 1: BMAD installs via npx\n   370→\n   371→​```bash\n   372→docker exec codeharness-verify npx bmad-method install --yes --tools claude-code\n   373→​```\n   374→\n   375→​```output\n   376→Installing BMAD Core agents and tools...\n   377→✓ Installed to _bmad/\n   378→​```\n   379→\n   380→**Verdict:** PASS\n   381→```\n   382→\n   383→### Agent-Browser Proof (Web App)\n   384→\n   385→```markdown\n   386→## AC 3: Login page renders and accepts credentials\n   387→\n   388→​```bash\n   389→docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser navigate http://localhost:3000/login\n   390→​```\n   391→\n   392→​```output\n   393→Navigated to http://localhost:3000/login (200 OK)\n   394→Page title: \"Login — MyApp\"\n   395→​```\n   396→\n   397→![Login page](screenshots/ac3-login-before.png)\n   398→\n   399→​```bash\n   400→docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=email-input]\"\n   401→docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser type \"test@example.com\"\n   402→docker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=submit-btn]\"\n   403→​```\n   404→\n   405→​```output\n   406→Clicked ref=email-input\n   407→Typed \"test@example.com\"\n   408→Clicked ref=submit-btn\n   409→Navigation: /login → /dashboard (302)\n   410→​```\n   411→\n   412→![After login](screenshots/ac3-login-after.png)\n   413→\n   414→**Verdict:** PASS — redirect to /dashboard confirms authentication\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→### OpenSearch Evidence\n   418→\n   419→```markdown\n   420→## AC 5: Runtime logs captured in OpenSearch\n   421→\n   422→​```bash\n   423→curl -s 'https://search.example.com/codeharness-logs/_search' \\\n   424→  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n   425→  -d '{\"query\":{\"match\":{\"service\":\"codeharness-verify\"}},\"size\":5}'\n   426→​```\n   427→\n   428→​```output\n   429→{\"hits\":{\"total\":{\"value\":23},\"hits\":[\n   430→  {\"_source\":{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T03:42:15Z\",\"level\":\"info\",\"message\":\"init complete\",\"service\":\"codeharness-verify\"}},\n   431→  ...\n   432→]}}\n   433→​```\n   434→\n   435→**Verdict:** PASS — 23 log entries from verification session\n   436→```\n   437→\n   438→## Hook Interaction Patterns\n   439→\n   440→### PreToolUse: Commit Gate (Specific)\n   441→\n   442→```json\n   443→{\n   444→  \"decision\": \"block\",\n   445→  \"reason\": \"Cannot commit — 2 quality gates not met:\\n\\n  ✗ tests_passed: false → Run: npm test\\n  ✗ coverage_met: false → Run: npm test -- --coverage\\n\\nAfter tests pass:\\n  → codeharness state set tests_passed true\\n  → codeharness state set coverage_met true\"\n   446→}\n   447→```\n   448→\n   449→### PostToolUse: After Test Run\n   450→\n   451→```json\n   452→{\n   453→  \"message\": \"Tests completed. Next steps:\\n  → Query logs: curl 'localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream:{service=\\\"codeharness\\\"}&limit=5'\\n  → Update flag: codeharness state set tests_passed true\\n  → Check coverage: npm test -- --coverage\"\n   454→}\n   455→```\n   456→\n   457→### SessionStart: Health Check\n   458→\n   459→```json\n   460→{\n   461→  \"message\": \"Harness health: OK\\n  Docker: running (shared stack)\\n  Sprint: 17/65 done\\n  Current: 3-3 verifying\\n  Session flags: reset\"\n   462→}\n   463→```\n   464→\n   465→## Design Principles\n   466→\n   467→1. **One screen, full picture.** `codeharness status` shows everything — project state, active run, results, action items. No scrolling through multiple files.\n   468→2. **Progressive detail.** Status → story drill-down → proof document. Each level adds depth without repeating the previous level.\n   469→3. **Failures are specific.** Never \"exit code 124\". Always: story, AC, command, output, reason, suggested fix.\n   470→4. **Live visibility.** `--live` shows what's happening in real time. Background mode writes to a status file that `codeharness status` reads.\n   471→5. **Actionable everything.** Every `[FAIL]` has a `→` remedy. Every blocked story has a reason. Every action item has context.\n   472→6. **Project-agnostic.** The same UX works for CLI tools, web apps, libraries, plugins. Verification approach changes, output format doesn't.\n   473→7. **JSON everywhere.** `--json` on every command for programmatic consumption. Same information, machine-readable.\n   474→8. **Dense over verbose.** One `[OK]` line per completed step. Summaries, not paragraphs. The user is a senior developer, not a novice.\n   475→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019ny8ECB7uLgXDKVNYx1sev","session_id":"e1f3df9b-d919-466e-880e-1001c8652ee8","uuid":"84467618-fae0-4d02-bc26-3099fb8a94e9","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:37:12.070Z"}
