{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019ny8ECB7uLgXDKVNYx1sev","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.md`.\n\n**Story Details:**\n- Story ID: 3.1\n- Story Key: 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions\n- File: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.md`\n- Status: ready-for-dev\n- Sprint status NOT modified (per user instruction)\n- Epic 3 status NOT modified (per user instruction)\n\n**What was created:**\n- 7 acceptance criteria covering: full dimension output, per-dimension status+metric, <30s performance, JSON output, gap descriptions with fixes, graceful degradation, and init guard\n- 7 task groups with detailed subtasks: types, dimension checkers, coordinator, report formatter, CLI command, unit tests, integration verification\n- Dev notes with architecture references, existing code reuse map, dependency chain, file size estimates, and previous story intelligence from 2.3\n\n**Verification tags applied:**\n- All 7 ACs tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` -- every AC can be verified by running `codeharness audit` (with or without `--json`) in a subprocess and inspecting output\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No integration-required ACs:** All ACs for this story describe CLI command output that can be verified by running the command in a subprocess. None require external system interactions, user sessions, or workflow orchestration. This is correct for a coordinator command, but worth noting that the runtime observability dimension check *internally* depends on an observability backend -- however the AC tests the graceful degradation path (warn when unavailable), which IS cli-verifiable.\n- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated.** Per user instruction, sprint-status.yaml was not modified. The workflow normally updates `3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions` from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev` and `epic-3` from `backlog` to `in-progress`. This must be done manually or in a subsequent step.\n- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension is underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile rule validation, but this story needs *something* for the infrastructure dimension. I scoped it to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks\" which is a reasonable placeholder, but the AC doesn't explicitly define what \"basic\" means. The dev agent has discretion here.\n- **Observation: No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** The UX spec covers `status`, `run`, `init`, `verify`, and `onboard` but not `audit` as a separate command. The PRD (FR21) says \"structured output (human-readable and --json)\" and NFR5 says \"follows UX spec format.\" I derived the output format from the existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`) which is consistent but not explicitly spec'd for audit."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1f0af1a7b4ff5f05 (use SendMessage with to: 'a1f0af1a7b4ff5f05' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72064\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 185585</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1f3df9b-d919-466e-880e-1001c8652ee8","uuid":"284b41de-5ee9-4eb2-b70c-d7526f3cc182","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:39:47.944Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do