ons (`gap()`, `dimOk()`, `dimCatch()`, `worstStatus()`) and compacting verbose gap-pushing blocks. The compacted style is less readable than the original but necessary for the constraint.\n- **CLI command test initially failed** because Commander throws `process.exit` on unknown commands when not using `exitOverride()`. Fixed by matching the existing onboard.test.ts pattern with `exitOverride()` and try/catch.\n- **One transient test run** showed 2 failing test files (5 tests) that passed on immediate re-run. Likely a timing/flake issue in the existing test suite, not related to this story's changes.\n- **Task 7.5 (\"verify audit runs on codeharness itself\")** was verified via build + test suite passing, but not via actual CLI invocation (`npx codeharness audit`) since that would require a real initialized project with state file. The tests thoroughly cover this path.\n- **Coverage target: 100%** is claimed based on test structure covering all branches, but was not measured with an actual coverage report on just the new files. The test suite covers all code paths (pass/fail/warn for each dimension, error handling, JSON/human output, precondition failures)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7d45827abcbd8893 (use SendMessage with to: 'a7d45827abcbd8893' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 118901\ntool_uses: 77\nduration_ms: 630998</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1f3df9b-d919-466e-880e-1001c8652ee8","uuid":"58d117c5-5e50-424e-8fd0-850123e754cc","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:50:52.825Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` sect