{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018C778EcLtq7WDJ74G9hiaw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<workflow>\n     2→  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3→  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4→  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5→  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6→\n     7→  <critical>🔥 YOU ARE AN ADVERSARIAL CODE REVIEWER - Find what's wrong or missing! 🔥</critical>\n     8→  <critical>Your purpose: Validate story file claims against actual implementation</critical>\n     9→  <critical>Challenge everything: Are tasks marked [x] actually done? Are ACs really implemented?</critical>\n    10→  <critical>Find 3-10 specific issues in every review minimum - no lazy \"looks good\" reviews - YOU are so much better than the dev agent\n    11→    that wrote this slop</critical>\n    12→  <critical>Read EVERY file in the File List - verify implementation against story requirements</critical>\n    13→  <critical>Tasks marked complete but not done = CRITICAL finding</critical>\n    14→  <critical>Acceptance Criteria not implemented = HIGH severity finding</critical>\n    15→  <critical>Do not review files that are not part of the application's source code. Always exclude the _bmad/ and _bmad-output/ folders from the review. Always exclude IDE and CLI configuration folders like .cursor/ and .windsurf/ and .claude/</critical>\n    16→\n    17→\n    18→  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Load story and discover changes\">\n    19→    <action>Use provided {{story_path}} or ask user which story file to review</action>\n    20→    <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    21→    <action>Set {{story_key}} = extracted key from filename (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication.md\" → \"1-2-user-authentication\") or story\n    22→      metadata</action>\n    23→    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Agent Record → File List, Change Log</action>\n    24→\n    25→    <!-- Discover actual changes via git -->\n    26→    <action>Check if git repository detected in current directory</action>\n    27→    <check if=\"git repository exists\">\n    28→      <action>Run `git status --porcelain` to find uncommitted changes</action>\n    29→      <action>Run `git diff --name-only` to see modified files</action>\n    30→      <action>Run `git diff --cached --name-only` to see staged files</action>\n    31→      <action>Compile list of actually changed files from git output</action>\n    32→    </check>\n    33→\n    34→    <!-- Cross-reference story File List vs git reality -->\n    35→    <action>Compare story's Dev Agent Record → File List with actual git changes</action>\n    36→    <action>Note discrepancies:\n    37→      - Files in git but not in story File List\n    38→      - Files in story File List but no git changes\n    39→      - Missing documentation of what was actually changed\n    40→    </action>\n    41→\n    42→    <invoke-protocol name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n    43→    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards (if exists)</action>\n    44→  </step>\n    45→\n    46→  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Build review attack plan\">\n    47→    <action>Extract ALL Acceptance Criteria from story</action>\n    48→    <action>Extract ALL Tasks/Subtasks with completion status ([x] vs [ ])</action>\n    49→    <action>From Dev Agent Record → File List, compile list of claimed changes</action>\n    50→\n    51→    <action>Create review plan:\n    52→      1. **AC Validation**: Verify each AC is actually implemented\n    53→      2. **Task Audit**: Verify each [x] task is really done\n    54→      3. **Code Quality**: Security, performance, maintainability\n    55→      4. **Test Quality**: Real tests vs placeholder bullshit\n    56→    </action>\n    57→  </step>\n    58→\n    59→  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Execute adversarial review\">\n    60→    <critical>VALIDATE EVERY CLAIM - Check git reality vs story claims</critical>\n    61→\n    62→    <!-- Git vs Story Discrepancies -->\n    63→    <action>Review git vs story File List discrepancies:\n    64→      1. **Files changed but not in story File List** → MEDIUM finding (incomplete documentation)\n    65→      2. **Story lists files but no git changes** → HIGH finding (false claims)\n    66→      3. **Uncommitted changes not documented** → MEDIUM finding (transparency issue)\n    67→    </action>\n    68→\n    69→    <!-- Use combined file list: story File List + git discovered files -->\n    70→    <action>Create comprehensive review file list from story File List and git changes</action>\n    71→\n    72→    <!-- AC Validation -->\n    73→    <action>For EACH Acceptance Criterion:\n    74→      1. Read the AC requirement\n    75→      2. Search implementation files for evidence\n    76→      3. Determine: IMPLEMENTED, PARTIAL, or MISSING\n    77→      4. If MISSING/PARTIAL → HIGH SEVERITY finding\n    78→    </action>\n    79→\n    80→    <!-- Task Completion Audit -->\n    81→    <action>For EACH task marked [x]:\n    82→      1. Read the task description\n    83→      2. Search files for evidence it was actually done\n    84→      3. **CRITICAL**: If marked [x] but NOT DONE → CRITICAL finding\n    85→      4. Record specific proof (file:line)\n    86→    </action>\n    87→\n    88→    <!-- Code Quality Deep Dive -->\n    89→    <action>For EACH file in comprehensive review list:\n    90→      1. **Security**: Look for injection risks, missing validation, auth issues\n    91→      2. **Performance**: N+1 queries, inefficient loops, missing caching\n    92→      3. **Error Handling**: Missing try/catch, poor error messages\n    93→      4. **Code Quality**: Complex functions, magic numbers, poor naming\n    94→      5. **Test Quality**: Are tests real assertions or placeholders?\n    95→    </action>\n    96→\n    97→    <check if=\"total_issues_found lt 3\">\n    98→      <critical>NOT LOOKING HARD ENOUGH - Find more problems!</critical>\n    99→      <action>Re-examine code for:\n   100→        - Edge cases and null handling\n   101→        - Architecture violations\n   102→        - Documentation gaps\n   103→        - Integration issues\n   104→        - Dependency problems\n   105→        - Git commit message quality (if applicable)\n   106→      </action>\n   107→      <action>Find at least 3 more specific, actionable issues</action>\n   108→    </check>\n   109→  </step>\n   110→\n   111→  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Present findings and fix them\">\n   112→    <action>Categorize findings: HIGH (must fix), MEDIUM (should fix), LOW (nice to fix)</action>\n   113→    <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   114→    <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   115→\n   116→    <output>**🔥 CODE REVIEW FINDINGS, {user_name}!**\n   117→\n   118→      **Story:** {{story_file}}\n   119→      **Git vs Story Discrepancies:** {{git_discrepancy_count}} found\n   120→      **Issues Found:** {{high_count}} High, {{medium_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   121→\n   122→      ## 🔴 CRITICAL ISSUES\n   123→      - Tasks marked [x] but not actually implemented\n   124→      - Acceptance Criteria not implemented\n   125→      - Story claims files changed but no git evidence\n   126→      - Security vulnerabilities\n   127→\n   128→      ## 🟡 MEDIUM ISSUES\n   129→      - Files changed but not documented in story File List\n   130→      - Uncommitted changes not tracked\n   131→      - Performance problems\n   132→      - Poor test coverage/quality\n   133→      - Code maintainability issues\n   134→\n   135→      ## 🟢 LOW ISSUES\n   136→      - Code style improvements\n   137→      - Documentation gaps\n   138→      - Git commit message quality\n   139→    </output>\n   140→\n   141→    <ask>What should I do with these issues?\n   142→\n   143→      1. **Fix them automatically** - I'll update the code and tests\n   144→      2. **Create action items** - Add to story Tasks/Subtasks for later\n   145→      3. **Show me details** - Deep dive into specific issues\n   146→\n   147→      Choose [1], [2], or specify which issue to examine:</ask>\n   148→\n   149→    <check if=\"user chooses 1\">\n   150→      <action>Fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues in the code</action>\n   151→      <action>Add/update tests as needed</action>\n   152→      <action>Update File List in story if files changed</action>\n   153→      <action>Update story Dev Agent Record with fixes applied</action>\n   154→      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = number of HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed</action>\n   155→      <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n   156→    </check>\n   157→\n   158→    <check if=\"user chooses 2\">\n   159→      <action>Add \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection to Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   160→      <action>For each issue: `- [ ] [AI-Review][Severity] Description [file:line]`</action>\n   161→      <action>Set {{action_count}} = number of action items created</action>\n   162→      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n   163→    </check>\n   164→\n   165→    <check if=\"user chooses 3\">\n   166→      <action>Show detailed explanation with code examples</action>\n   167→      <action>Return to fix decision</action>\n   168→    </check>\n   169→  </step>\n   170→\n   171→  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:review-enforcement -->\n   172→  <step n=\"4.5\" goal=\"Harness verification checks\">\n   173→    <critical>Codeharness requires these additional review checks</critical>\n   174→    <action>Verify Showboat proof document exists at docs/exec-plans/active/{{story_key}}.proof.md or docs/exec-plans/completed/{{story_key}}.proof.md</action>\n   175→    <action>Check AGENTS.md freshness — all modules in File List must have up-to-date AGENTS.md</action>\n   176→    <action>Verify test coverage meets 100% target for all changed modules</action>\n   177→    <action if=\"proof document missing\">Add HIGH finding: \"Missing Showboat proof document\"</action>\n   178→    <action if=\"AGENTS.md stale or missing for changed module\">Add MEDIUM finding: \"AGENTS.md missing or stale for {{module}}\"</action>\n   179→    <action if=\"coverage below target\">Add HIGH finding: \"Test coverage below 100% target\"</action>\n   180→  </step>\n   181→  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:review-enforcement -->\n   182→\n   183→  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Update story status and sync sprint tracking\">\n   184→    <!-- Determine new status based on review outcome -->\n   185→    <check if=\"all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed AND all ACs implemented\">\n   186→      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"done\"</action>\n   187→      <action>Update story Status field to \"done\"</action>\n   188→    </check>\n   189→    <check if=\"HIGH or MEDIUM issues remain OR ACs not fully implemented\">\n   190→      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   191→      <action>Update story Status field to \"in-progress\"</action>\n   192→    </check>\n   193→    <action>Save story file</action>\n   194→\n   195→    <!-- Determine sprint tracking status -->\n   196→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n   197→      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"enabled\"</action>\n   198→    </check>\n   199→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist\">\n   200→      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   201→    </check>\n   202→\n   203→    <!-- Sync sprint-status.yaml when story status changes (only if sprint tracking enabled) -->\n   204→    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   205→      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   206→      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   207→\n   208→      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'done'\">\n   209→        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"done\"</action>\n   210→        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   211→        <output>✅ Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} → done</output>\n   212→      </check>\n   213→\n   214→      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'in-progress'\">\n   215→        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   216→        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n   217→        <output>🔄 Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} → in-progress</output>\n   218→      </check>\n   219→\n   220→      <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   221→        <output>⚠️ Story file updated, but sprint-status sync failed: {{story_key}} not found in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   222→      </check>\n   223→    </check>\n   224→\n   225→    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   226→      <output>ℹ️ Story status updated (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   227→    </check>\n   228→\n   229→    <output>**✅ Review Complete!**\n   230→\n   231→      **Story Status:** {{new_status}}\n   232→      **Issues Fixed:** {{fixed_count}}\n   233→      **Action Items Created:** {{action_count}}\n   234→\n   235→      {{#if new_status == \"done\"}}Code review complete!{{else}}Address the action items and continue development.{{/if}}\n   236→    </output>\n   237→  </step>\n   238→\n   239→</workflow>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UmDTVZ4iS72Xuw7ncmN4YZ","session_id":"e1f3df9b-d919-466e-880e-1001c8652ee8","uuid":"0d17301c-9ed1-447e-b534-c0894b8814e5","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:51:52.988Z"}
